The paper deals with the computation of Wasserstein barycenters of persistence diagrams, which are commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and computer vision (cs.CV) for shape analysis and feature extraction. The paper also presents an application to ensemble clustering, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and scalability of the proposed algorithm, which is relevant to the field of scientific computing (cs.SI).
